Contributed work merged from upstream pull requests
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Apple Silicon and macOS Tahoe support in this fork is derived from work
published as pull requests against the upstream project. Their authors did the
hard part; this fork integrates, fixes and extends it.

Jeffrey Reisberg (@sparc5)
  https://github.com/rlxone/MultiSoundChanger/pull/41
  - Removal of the x86_64-only compiled OSD.framework binary and the
    EXCLUDED_ARCHS = arm64 workaround, enabling native Apple Silicon builds
  - Custom VolumeHUD replacing the dead private OSD HUD path
  - HID-level volume key remapping via hidutil (MediaKeyRemapper)
  - Vendored MediaKeyTap with F18/F19/F20 mapping, replacing the CocoaPods
    dependency

juniq (@juniqlim)
  https://github.com/rlxone/MultiSoundChanger/pull/40
  - Volume percentage label next to the menu bar slider
  - Treating mute as a state distinct from zero volume in the HUD

